To Use:
Clone this repository to your home directory:
cd ~
git clone https://github.com/akioito/dotfiles.git
mkdir .vim
ln -s dotfiles/vimrc .vimrc
ln -s dotfiles/gvimrc .gvimrc
cp -r dotfiles/mybundle .vim/mybundle
curl https://raw.githubusercontent.com/Shougo/neobundle.vim/master/bin/install.sh | sh

--------------------------------------------------
Environment:
MacVim compiled as following:
git clone https://github.com/macvim-dev/macvim.git
cd macvim
sudo xcode-select --switch /Applications/Xcode9.4.1.app # if you are in Mojave, see Special Install bellow
CFLAGS=-O3 ./configure --enable-python3interp 
make

--------------------------------------------------
fish shell
cd macvim
git pull
make distclean
sudo xcode-select --switch /Applications/Xcode9.4.1.app # if you are in Mojave, see Special Install bellow
set -x CFLAGS -O3; ./configure --enable-python3interp
make

--------------------------------------------------
Mojave / XCode 10 Special Install (until this is resolved: https://github.com/macvim-dev/macvim/pull/757)
git clone -b fix-the-flicker --single-branch https://github.com/s4y/macvim
cd macvim
set -x CFLAGS -O3; ./configure  --enable-python3interp
make

---------------
Symlink (Only for first time)
cd /Applications
ln -s $HOME/macvim/src/MacVim/build/Release/MacVim.app .
--------------------------------------------------
Assume previous installs:
XCode9.4.1 (https://developer.apple.com/download/more/) # For Mojave
XCode10 #  see Special Install above
HomeBrew
Python3.6.5 (https://www.python.org/downloads/release/python-365/  macOS 64-bit installer)


--------------------------------------------------
Visual trick:
defaults write org.vim.MacVim MMTextInsetLeft  5
defaults write org.vim.MacVim MMTextInsetRight 2


--------------------------------------------------
Usual commands:
Normal mode
unu for NeoBundle Update
Ctl-L  for Buffer navigation
F3  for global search word (Cmd J/Cmd K for navigation) / F4 Close quick fix 
Shift Cursor Select and Enter for Align column
Cmd-1 for Comment/Uncomment
As usual, for other commands see vimrc

--------------------------------------------------
Project management
see mybundle/vim-project-files or https://github.com/akioito/vim-project-files 
open sample.vim-prj
:PyOpenProject

--------------------------------------------------



